data.chText: （书刊或纸张的）页，面，张，版
data.enText: one side or both sides of a sheet of paper in a book, magazine, etc.

data.chText: 请翻到第64页。
data.enText: Turn to page 64.

data.chText: 有人从这本书里撕掉了一张。
data.enText: Someone has torn a page out of this book.

data.chText: 空白页；新的一页
data.enText: a blank/new page

data.chText: 报纸的体育 / 财经版
data.enText: the sports/financial pages of the newspaper

data.chText: 在对面的一页上
data.enText: on the opposite/facing page

data.chText: 在下一页
data.enText: over the page (= on the next page)

data.chText: （计算机的）页面，版面
data.enText: a section of data or information that can be shown on a computer screen at any one time

data.chText: 历史篇章，历史篇页（指历史大事或时期）
data.enText: an important event or period of history

data.chText: 阿拉伯历史上光辉的篇章
data.enText: a glorious page of Arab history

data.chText: （美国议员的）青年助理（本身为学生）
data.enText: a student who works as an assistant to a member of the US Congress

data.chText: 学习骑士（接受训练期间做侍从，可晋升骑士）
data.enText: a boy or young man who worked for a knight while training to be a knight himself
on the same page

data.chText: 目标一致；就目标达成共识
data.enText: if two or more people or groups are on the same page , they agree about what they are trying to achieve
turn the page

data.chText: （经过困难后）翻开新的一页，开始新的生活
data.enText: to begin doing things in a different way and thinking in a more positive way after a period of difficulties

data.chText: 印在书报上的文字；书刊文字；印刷品
data.enText: what is published in books, newspapers, etc.

data.chText: 书刊文字的力量
data.enText: the power of the printed word

data.chText: （在公共传呼系统上）呼叫
data.enText: to call sb's name over a public address system in order to find them and give them a message

data.chText: 你为何不在机场扩音喇叭上呼叫他呢？
data.enText: Why don't you have him paged at the airport?

data.chText: 用传呼机传呼（某人）
data.enText: to contact sb by sending a message to their pager

data.chText: 请立即传呼格林医生。
data.enText: Page Dr Green immediately.

data.enText: to quickly turn the pages of a book, magazine, etc. and look at them without reading them carefully or in detail

tr: one side of one leaf (of a book or magazine or newspaper or letter etc.) or the written or pictorial matter it contains
in medieval times a youth acting as a knight's attendant as the first stage in training for knighthood
a youthful attendant at official functions or ceremonies such as legislative functions and weddings
a boy who is employed to run errands
contact, as with a pager or by calling somebody's name over a P.A. system
number the pages of a book or manuscript

example: He is paging in Congress this summer

value.def: A page is one side of one of the pieces of paper in a book, magazine, or newspaper. Each page usually has a number printed at the top or bottom.

example.ex: Where's your book? Take it out and turn to page 4.
example.tran: 你的书呢？拿出来，翻到第4页。

value.def: The pages of a book, magazine, or newspaper are the pieces of paper it consists of.

example.ex: He turned the pages of his notebook...
Over the page you can read all about the six great books on offer.
example.tran: 在下一页上，你可以看到有关6本在售好书的全部信息。

value.def: You can refer to an important event or period of time as a page of history.

example.ex: ...a new page in the country's political history.
example.tran: 该国政治史上崭新的一页

value.tran: （历史的）一页（指重大事件或重要时期）

value.def: If someone who is in a public place is paged, they receive a message, often over a speaker, telling them that someone is trying to contact them.

example.ex: He was paged repeatedly as the flight was boarding...
example.tran: 航班登机时，广播里反复呼叫他。

example.ex: I'll have them paged and tell them you're here.
example.tran: 我会叫人呼他们，告诉他们你在这儿。

value.def: A page is a small boy who accompanies the bride at a wedding.
value.tran: （婚礼上新娘的）男伴童，小男傧相

value.boxr_value: in BRIT, use 英国英语用 pageboy

value.def: A page is a young person who takes messages or does small jobs for members of the United States Congress or state legislatures.
value.tran: （美国国会或州立法会的）青年助理

value.def: In former times, a page was a young boy who was a knight's servant and was learning to be a knight.
value.tran: （旧时做骑士侍从的）实习骑士
